{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bf15fc7c-65c2-499f-8c32-a1f8f20d4cb1","content":"In .NET MAUI, you configure platform lifecycle event mappings in your `MauiProgram.cs` using `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* your code */ })\n        .OnStop(activity => { /* your code */ }));\n#elif IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* your code */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Use `#if ANDROID` / `#elif IOS` preprocessor directives to keep platform code separated.\n- Each platform exposes its native events (e.g., `OnResume`, `OnDestroy` on Android; `WillEnterForeground`, `WillTerminate` on iOS).\n- The delegates receive the native platform object (`Activity` on Android, `UIApplication` on iOS).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ed48b358-5a0d-4fcc-acd0-ae5c3b3cf67a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI - specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":339,"requestId":"A84B:6D183:650D83:752FC7:69FBE2E9"},"id":"9b98be82-39c1-4652-befc-425e7d8e88b3","timestamp":"2026-05-07T00:55:12.156Z","parentId":"7921f6f8-1d7e-41e8-b7d8-24ce0bd3451e"}
